# ==============================================================
# Docker build context excludes.
#
# Goal: send only what the Dockerfile actually needs
#   - clojure/ sources + deps.edn + resources
#   - data/ tars + canonical-greekLit / canonical-latinLit corpora
#   - pyproject.toml, README.md, uv.lock, src/
# ...and NOT the multi-hundred-MB artifacts that are rebuilt in
# the image (or are pure dev cruft). Keep this in sync with the
# large/generated paths in .gitignore.
# ==============================================================

# --- VCS / CI / editor ---
.git
.github
.gitignore
.dockerignore
Dockerfile
deploy
docs
notebooks

# --- Python dev environment & caches ---
.venv
.pdm-python
.pytest_cache
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
tests

# --- Stale, gitignored index artifacts (not read at runtime) ---
src/*.pkl
src/*.json

# --- Large morph data rebuilt from the .tar archives in-image ---
# (the .tar files themselves ARE needed, so don't exclude those)
data/*.jsonl
data/*.morph.xml
data/*.ls.perseus-eng2.xml
data/*.perseus-eng1.xml

# --- Clojure build outputs (morph.db is rebuilt in stage 1) ---
clojure/morph.db
clojure/*.db-journal
clojure/*.db-wal
clojure/*.db-shm
clojure/.cpcache
clojure/.nrepl-port
